With partial nationalisation, the Benelux States are helping, as the first European, the Belgian-Dutch bank in distress due to the spillover effect of the US credit market crisis, Fortison: the three countries are supporting the financial and insurance institution, which also has interests in Hungary, with a total of EUR 11.2 billion.
